</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<hr>
<br>
        <br>
        <b>POPULAR POETS</b><br>
        <br>
<p>
This category represents the total number of points awarded each poet for their entire body of work in Volume XIII. The most poems an individual can have accepted in <i>The Nest</i> each year is eight. Obviously, the more 
poems a person publishes, the greater chances she or he had of attracting votes. No poet had eight poems in Volume XIII. Two poets had seven poems and three had six.
</p>
<p>
To put into perspective how well the winners did: we published poems by 250 poets during 2011 and the average total points for combined works this year was 15.
</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<br> <strong>GRAND PRIZE:</strong><br>POET OF THE YEAR (20 nominations, naming 4 of 7 poems published in Volume XIII = 135 points)<br> <br> <strong>Carolyn Hall</strong><br><br>
        <p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><b>&nbsp;</b></p>
        First Runner-up: (17 nominations, naming 3 of 3 poems published = 110 points)<br> <br> <strong>Chen-ou Liu</strong><br> <br> <br> 
        Second Runner-up: (21 votes for 4 of 4 poems = 129 points)<br> <br> <strong>Jim Kacian</strong><br><br><br>
        Third Runner-up (tie): 15 nominations, naming 4 of 5 poems published = 106 points)<br> <br> <strong>Michael McClintock</strong><br><br>
        (16 nominations, naming 3 of 5 poems published = 106 points)<br> <br> <strong>Chad Lee Robinson</strong><br>
<br>
